{"uuid": "5af23756-c610-428f-8b02-ed3706e7752a", "id": 31070, "date": "2021-11-29T05:00:00", "date_gmt": "2021-11-29T13:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "https://estreetshuffle.com/?p=31070"}, "modified": "2024-01-02T21:30:12", "modified_gmt": "2024-01-03T05:30:12", "slug": "matr-john-legend-bruce-springsteen-billy-joel-and-india-arie-signed-sealed-delivered-im-yours", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2021/11/29/matr-john-legend-bruce-springsteen-billy-joel-and-india-arie-signed-sealed-delivered-im-yours/", "title": {"rendered": "MatR: John Legend, Bruce Springsteen, Billy Joel, and India Arie: Signed, Sealed, Delivered I&#8217;m Yours"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Stevie Wonder&#8217;s &#8220;Signed, Sealed, Delivered I&#8217;m Yours&#8221; was a smash hit from the beginning, topping the U.S. R&amp;B chart for six weeks and peaking at #3 on the Hot 100 in 1970.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Stevie Wonder - Signed, Sealed, Delivered I&#039;m Yours\" width=\"758\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/pUj9frKY46E?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>The song signaled an inflection point in Wonder&#8217;s career on the wings of a new creative confidence and artistic control over his work.</p>\n<p>But &#8220;Signed, Sealed, Delivered I&#8217;m Yours&#8221; earned a more permanent place in history in 2008, when U.S. presidential candidate (and Bruce&#8217;s future BFF) Barack Obama embraced it as his campaign&#8217;s theme song all the way through Election Day and his first on-stage appearance in Grant Park as president-elect.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Obama Grant Park Rally - Signed Sealed Delivered\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/iUqwkgyLv-8?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>The Obama campaign played Wonder&#8217;s 1970 single at virtually every rally that election season, so when Bruce Springsteen, Billy Joel, John Legend, and India Arie banded together in support of Obama during the final push, there was really only one song they could have chosen to end the night on.</p>\n<p>Bruce and Billy&#8217;s main set has been circulating broadly for a while now, but the encores are a bit harder to come by. So take a listen and enjoy the exuberant finale of the\u00a0<em>Change Rocks!\u00a0</em>benefit from October 16, 2008, featuring Legend and Arie on lead vocals, with support from Bruce on guitar and Billy on piano.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-31070-2\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Signed-Sealed-2008-10-16.mp3?_=2\" /><a href=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Signed-Sealed-2008-10-16.mp3\">https://estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Signed-Sealed-2008-10-16.mp3</a></audio>\n<p>And if audio from that performance is rare, video is scarcer still. But check this out: it&#8217;s only about a minute or so, but it&#8217;s enough to capture the energy and excitement in the room that night, and the anticipation of eight years to come.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Barack Obama Signed, Sealed &amp; Delivered at NYC Change Rocks\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Gz20pPR3yXU?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p><strong>Signed, Sealed, Delivered I&#8217;m Yours<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> October 16, 2008 (New York City, NY)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> October 16, 2008 (New York City, NY)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One time only: John Legend, India Arie, Billy Joel, and Bruce Springsteen join forces on an anticipatory, celebratory cover of Stevie Wonder&#8217;s 1970 classic. </p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 31149, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [4, 5], "tags": [1662, 669, 3351, 1723, 2447, 3352, 2275], "class_list": ["post-31070", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-barack-obama", "tag-billy-joel", "tag-india-arie", "tag-john-legend", "tag-michelle-obama", "tag-signed-sealed-delivered-im-yours", "tag-stevie-wonder"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/signedsealed.jpg?fit=820%2C820&s